    "It provides a measure of the extent of how much deviation agents are making from their optimal path.",
    "It can be derived as follow:",
    "where L(n) is the generated path's length of agent n, and L A * (n) is the agent n's shortest path, which is calculated with the A* algorithm by only considering the single-agent path planning problem with static obstacles.",
    "In other words, it measures the additional distance that agents must travel due to the presence of other agents or dynamic obstacles.",
